race.comment: OLIVIA'S SCANDAL (5) goes on top to close out the card. She's racing in ultra-consistent form and is rarely far away, She just missed when last seen at Donald, going down by a nose and this won't take any more winning if she gets some luck from the wide gate. TRAK CHILLER (10) resumes for a new yard. She didn't fire last preparation but her older form would see her well placed in this and she might be worth keeping an eye on if the market likes her. MISSISSIPPI MILLER (7) can mix her form, solid at Donald last time having been close up at Kyneton prior. She looks a good each way hope. SEATTLE HOPE (8) was poor last time but is right in this on the second placing at Echuca prior. JUICE BOX (1) has been solid in two runs since coming down from Darwin and is in the mix.
